Norman YAWNICK, Adm’r of Estate of Carl Yawnick, Deceased, v. INDEPENDENT FOOD PRODUCTS CO., a Corporation of New Jersey, Edith Elkind, Samuel Rosenbaum, Sidney Rosenbaum and Israel Rosenbaum. Appeal of Louis SHERMAN. No. 7871. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Argued Feb. 6, 1942. Decided Feb. 6, 1942. Louis A. Fast, of Newark, N. J., for appellant. George Such Pearse, of Newark, N. J., for appellee.

Before MARIS, JONES, and GOODRICH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The appeal is dismissed.
